  <h1>About Free Ham Radio Curriculum</h1>

  <h2>What this is</h2>
  <p>
    Free Ham Radio Curriculum is a free, open curriculum of workshops and activities that take learners from no
    radio experience toward confident HF operation. Materials include slides, learner handouts,
    trainer guides, and promo copy — built so any experienced Ham can lead a session with minimal
    prep.
  </p>

  <h2>Why this matters</h2>
  <p>
    People want to learn radio — for emergency preparation, for fun, or just out of curiosity — and experienced Hams are usually
    happy to help. The bottleneck is not a lack of passion. It is curriculum: most existing
    material, in print or online, targets individuals studying for license exams, while guides for club events assume you
    already know how to organize a group session. What's needed is a planned path to take groups of radio-curious novices from no
    experience to confident HF operation, with materials any Ham can teach with minimal prep.
  </p>
  <p>
    That is what this project provides. Workshops and activities are built so that one passionate operator
    can teach ten, twenty, or more learners — even someone who has never taught adults, even when the
    learners have never touched a radio. New Hams should not have to find their way into the hobby
    alone. This curriculum is how we bring many new people into radio, together.
  </p>

  <h2>What this is not</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Not license test prep — there's plenty of that material out there</li>
    <li>Not for individuals - it's for the (many) learners who learn best in community</li>
    <li>Not an online course — these materials are for in-person groups</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Independence</h2>
  <p>
    Free Ham Radio Curriculum is an independent project. It is non-partisan and not affiliated with any
    organization except a pending grant application to{' '}
    <a href="https://www.ampr.org/" rel="noopener noreferrer">ARDC</a> (Amateur Radio Digital
    Communications).
  </p>

